===Logic:Separate midi notes by channel or pitch===
----

Select the MIDI region you would like to affect and then go to the '''MIDI''' menu and choose '''Separate MIDI events''', then choose the option you want. (image below)

[[File:Logic separate note by pitch or channel.png]]


----

In some earlier versions of Logic this process of s separating notes by pitch or channel '''demixing'''

You can '''demix''' MIDI notes by selecting the MIDI region you wish
to demix and then going to: 

'''Region''' then '''Split / Demix'''


Then choose to '''Demix By Event Channel''' or '''Demix By Note Pitch''' 


[[Image:Logic Pro demix.png]]





